- Accessibility:
  - All interactive controls have ARIA labels
  - Keyboard navigable, focus states clearly visible
- Performance:
  - Debounced or throttled search
  - Lazy loading lists if large
  - Use memoization to prevent unnecessary rerenders
- Runtime safety:
  - Always guard against null/undefined values when using arrays
  - Example: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Initialize all array states with []: useState<MyType[]>([])
- State and Data flow:
  - Role-aware rendering: show/hide widgets based on user role from auth/permissions
  - Data normalization: standardize date formats, currency, and IDs client-side
  - Persist user date range preference for revenue snapshot per user (optional)

### Backend
