=== TASK ===
# Dashboard

## Overview
Create a role-aware, enterprise-grade Dashboard for LuxeFlow CRM that surfaces time-critical operational data and enables quick actions. The page should present a set of widgets including Operations Command Center, upcoming stays, payment due list, overdue tasks, revenue/commission snapshot, alerts, and quick actions. It must integrate with existing authentication and authorization, respect permissions per role (Admin, Agent, Ops, Finance), and provide a smooth, premium user experience aligned with LuxeFlow’s luxury design system. All data handling must be resilient to null/undefined values and guarded against runtime errors as per the mandatory runtime safety rules.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Dashboard is the Role-aware home screen for LuxeFlow users. Its goals are to give each user a consolidated, at-a-glance view of time-sensitive work and performance metrics, plus fast access to common actions. Connected features include client management, bookings, payments, tasks, and alerts within the LuxeFlow CRM. UI should be information-dense yet approachable, with clear visual hierarchy and generous whitespace.

Key UI elements and guidance:
- Global header with:
  - Organization switcher (org-level scope)
  - User avatar and quick profile actions
  - Quick search field
- Operations Command Center widget:
  - Upcoming check-ins/check-outs within the next 7 days
  - Outstanding balances by due date
  - Overdue tasks
  - Approvals needed (e.g., VIP requests, vendor approvals)
- Upcoming Stays widget:
  - Mini calendar or list of upcoming stays with dates, client name, resort, room type
- Payment Due List widget:
  - List of payments due, with due date, amount, client, booking reference, payment status
- Overdue Tasks widget:
  - Top overdue tasks, assignees, due dates, SLA color tags
- Revenue/Commission Snapshot widget:
  - KPI cards: Bookings count, Gross Booking Value (GBV), Commission Earned
  - Date range selector (e.g., Last 7/30/90 days, custom)
- Alerts widget:
  - Time-sensitive alerts with priority, short description, due date
- Quick Actions widget:
  - Shortcuts: New Client, New Booking, Create Task, Search Resort
- AI Assistant Quick Access Button:
  - Nearby chat/button to trigger AI assistant for insights or drafting tasks and itineraries
- Visual behavior:
  - Sticky header with subtle fade
  - Cards with soft shadows, light borders, and rounded corners per design system
  - Hover states for interactive cards and actions
  - Data visualizations kept minimalist (monochrome or accent color emphasis) without clutter
- Responsiveness:
  - Desktop: grid layout with multiple widgets
  - Tablet/Mobile: reflow to stacked cards with accessible tap targets; collapsible sections as needed

## Components to Build
- DashboardLayout
  - Layout container, responsive grid, header integration, org/user switcher, search
- Widget: Operations Command Center
  - Sub-sections for upcoming checks, balances by due date, overdue tasks, approvals
- Widget: Upcoming Stays
  - Mini-calendar or compact list with key fields
- Widget: Payment Due List
  - Table or list with sorting by due date, status badges
- Widget: Overdue Tasks
  - List with task title, due date, assignee, priority
- Widget: Revenue Snapshot
  - KPI cards (Bookings, GBV, Commission) and date-range selector
- Widget: Alerts
  - List of alerts with priority, description, due date
- Widget: Quick Actions
  - Button set for Create actions
- Widget: AI Assistant Quick Access
  - Floating or prominent button to open AI assistant
- Data Helpers
  - Safe data fetch utilities, null guards, and formatting
- Shared UI Elements
  - Card, divider, button, input, select components that align with the design system
- State Management Hooks
  - useDashboardData (fetch and normalize dashboard data per role)
  - usePermissions (determine which widgets to show)

